race.comment: SOO KISS ME (4) is building nicely this time in, improving her finishing position by one each time she's stepped out. She was good at Wodonga two back when third and just missed at Balranald last time when well supported. The Duffy/Weeding combination is a good one on their home deck and she should go close. O'REG (1) is knocking on the door having just found one better his past two. Beaten a length last time at Wodonga, he gets a good jockey up and can roll forward. CHAIRMAN'S CHOICE (2) was behind O'REG last time at Wodonga when working home into third. He has to be considered off that effort. MAGNEA (3) was better last time at Wodonga in the same race and comes under notice now, although the draw is sticky.
